HEADWORD: Byelorussia
<hw>Byelorussia</hw> <pos>n.</pos> <def>a European country east of
Poland, formerly a part of the Soviet Union. After the breakup of the
Soviet Union the name was changed to
<altname>Belarus</altname>.</def>⟦br⟧
<syn><b>Syn. --</b> Belarus, Belorussia, White Russia.</syn>⟦br⟧
[<source>WordNet 1.5</source>]</p>

